==English==
===Etymology===
from '''Fars''', the Arabic name for the province of [[Persis]] ("[[w:Pars|Pars]]") in southwestern [[Iran]] (Arabic lacks the letter 'p'). The name was adopted by the Arabs and [[Persian]]s to refer to Persian language after the Islamic invasions of the 7th century.

